mminck]], 1844)</small> — inhabits [[Siberia]]<ref name="Mazak1981">{{cite journal |author=Mazák, V. |author-link=Vratislav Mazák |year=1981 |url=http://www.science.smith.edu/departments/Biology/VHAYSSEN/msi/pdf/i0076-3519-152-01-0001.pdf |title=''Panthera tigris'' |journal=Mammalian Species |volume=152 |issue=152 |pages=1–8 |doi=10.2307/3504004 |jstor=3504004 |access-date=2 February 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514122546/http://www.science.smith.edu/departments/Biology/VHAYSSEN/msi/pdf/i0076-3519-152-01-0001.pdf |archive-date=14 May 2011 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref> *[[Indochinese tiger]], formerly ''P. t. corbetti'' <small>[[Vratislav Mazák|Mazák]], 1968</small> — inhabits [[Southeast Asia]]<ref>{{cite journal |author=Mazák, V. |year=1968 |title=Nouvelle sous-espèce de tigre provenant de l'Asie du sud-est |journal=Mammalia |volume=32 |issue=1 |page=104}}</ref> *[[Malayan tiger]], formerly ''P. t. jacksoni'' <small>Luo et al., 2004</small> — inhabits [[Peninsular Malaysia]]<ref name="Iucn2015MT">{{IUCN |assessor= Kawanishi, K. |year=2015 |title=Panthera tigris subsp. jacksoni |id=136893 |version=2017-1}}</ref>
